ActRoyal Canadian Mounted Police Act
SubjectMunicipal Policing Services Transition Agreements
PrecisOrder approving that the Minister of Public Safety and Emergency Preparedness, on behalf of the Government of Canada, enter into an arrangement with British Columbia with respect to its municipalities, with each of the specified municipalities of Nova Scotia, New Brunswick, Manitoba and Prince Edward Island; and the regional policing authority established for the municipalities of Moncton, Dieppe and Riverview in New Brunswick for the use or employment of the Royal Canadian Mounted Police in aiding the administration of justice in those municipalities and in carrying into effect the laws in force there.
